  * In developpement...

 -- Sébastien Valat <sebastien.valat.dev@orange.fr>  Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:32:08 +0100

svunittest (0.4.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Many bug fixes.
  * Add some packaging example files (Gentoo, Arch Linux and Fedora)
  * Add new assertion SVUT_ASSERT_ZERO/SVUT_ASSERT_NO_ZERO
  * Add support of flat test with C like functions.
  * Add missing character escaping in XML formats.
  * Add support of JUnit XML output format.
  * Provide some scripts to quicly generate HTML reports.
  * Capture printf/puts/cout in tests (not in external libs up to now).

 -- Sébastien Valat <sebastien.valat.dev@orange.fr>  Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:32:08 +0100

svunittest (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low

   * Code cleanup to pass -pednatic on Linux gcc and icc.
   * SVUT_REGISTER_TEST_METHOD() do not need class name now.
   * Base files for ubuntu package.
   * Add some assertions : SVUT_ASSERT_GE, GT, LE, LT ...
   * Add macro SVUT_SET_CONTEXT() to help debugging failed tests.
   * Split sources into multiple directory to be more readable.
   * Bugfix problem with test case empty name.
   * Check C++0x compatibility on gcc, icc and clang.

 -- Sébastien Valat <sebastien.valat.dev@orange.fr>  Sun, 13 Mar 2011 14:04:34 +0100

svunittest (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * User documentation.
  * Usage examples (usage and build with cmake/autotools)
  * Portability fixes, test suite passed on windows + VCC/cygwin, Linux + gcc/clang/icc, FreeBSD + gcc.
  * CPPUnit is now optional to pass the test suite of svUnitTest : replaced by short implementation fakecppunit.
  * Add cmake/pkg_config integration files.
  * Replace glibc argument parsor (argp.h) by our own implementon for non glibc-systems portability (windows....).
  * Add terminal color support detection via isatty().
  * Fix naming issue related to xslt_html.
  * Fix valgrind memory leak reported in test suite.
  * Fix compilers warnings (clang/gcc/icc/vcc)

 -- Sébastien Valat <sebastien.valat.dev@orange.fr>  Sun, 27 Feb 2011 21:59:47 +0100

svunittest (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Base implementation
  * Unit tests of the base implementation
  * Output format : XML, Qt XML, Black & white stdout, Colored stdout
  * Provide most of the required assertions SVUT_ASSERT_EQUAL()...
  * Provide the INDEV and TODO state in addition to others unit test libraries.
  * Provide a basic XSLT file to manualy generate HTML from native XML output format.
  * Provide standelon of test suite predefine main functions.

 -- Sébastien Valat <sebastien.valat.dev@orange.fr>  Mon, 21 Feb 2011 18:42:19 +0100
